00:43:47.191 --> 00:43:49.854
That man should be in prison.
not a museum. He's a pedophile.

728
00:43:49.927 --> 00:43:53.659
[scoffs] You know. as much as I'd
love to stick around for another lecture

729
00:43:53.731 --> 00:43:56.826
about the moral bankruptcy of
modern Neo-Pop. I have to go.

730
00:43:57.268 --> 00:43:58.497
You don't have to do anything.

731
00:43:58.569 --> 00:44:00.538
Actually. Colin. I do.

732
00:44:00.605 --> 00:44:02.316
I have to make a living.
and sometimes that means

733
00:44:02.340 --> 00:44:03.617
interacting with
people who don't live up

734
00:44:03.641 --> 00:44:05.906
to your impossible
standard of artistic integrity.

735
00:44:06.544 --> 00:44:07.544
You like it.

736
00:44:07.678 --> 00:44:10.307
- What?
- Admit it. you like it.

737
00:44:10.481 --> 00:44:13.121
You like getting dressed up and
hanging out with the popular crowd.

738
00:44:14.785 --> 00:44:16.276
You think it makes you cool.

739
00:44:19.190 --> 00:44:21.352
You really can be such a dick.

740
00:44:27.498 --> 00:44:29.694
[lively chatter]

741
00:44:31.035 --> 00:44:33.595
[Andrea] Oh. my
God. Everybody's here.

742
00:44:34.472 --> 00:44:37.203
Um. if people ask if we're
sisters. just say yes. right?

743
00:44:37.275 --> 00:44:38.785
- [chuckles]
- I mean. wouldn't that be fun?

744
00:44:38.809 --> 00:44:40.107
- Sure. Andrea.
- Okay.

745
00:44:40.178 --> 00:44:41.669
Whatever you want.

746
00:44:54.492 --> 00:44:55.492
[clicks tongue]

747
00:44:56.327 --> 00:44:57.852
Here she is.

748
00:44:58.896 --> 00:45:00.660
Whitney Solloway.

749
00:45:02.266 --> 00:45:03.598
The one that got away.

750
00:45:04.302 --> 00:45:09.240
Oh. uh. my love. I must introduce
you to a dear friend of mine.

751
00:45:09.440 --> 00:45:10.567
Dashiell?

752
00:45:11.375 --> 00:45:12.375
Oh.

753
00:45:14.312 --> 00:45:16.304
- Dashiell Boucicault.
- Hi.

754
00:45:16.380 --> 00:45:18.144
Ah. Lindsay's mentioned you.

755
00:45:18.749 --> 00:45:19.749
Lindsay?

756
00:45:20.451 --> 00:45:23.580
Thanks. It's the name
my mama gave me.

757
00:45:23.654 --> 00:45:25.680
- [chuckles]
- Andrea Rossman.

758
00:45:25.756 --> 00:45:27.657
Whitney is my gallery assistant.

759
00:45:27.725 --> 00:45:29.387
Oh. Hello.

760
00:45:29.627 --> 00:45:32.290
[Andrea] I. uh. have been
a fan of yours for years.

761
00:45:32.363 --> 00:45:35.765
I would love to pick your brain
about the collection that you've built.

762
00:45:35.833 --> 00:45:37.631
Have you seen the Therrien?

763
00:45:37.702 --> 00:45:40.069
It will make you feel so small.

764
00:45:42.139 --> 00:45:46.167
He's a very important collector.

765
00:45:46.944 --> 00:45:48.537
- Do you know him?
- No.

766
00:45:49.847 --> 00:45:52.248
Uh. he's opening a
new gallery in New York.

767
00:45:52.850 --> 00:45:55.979
I'm hoping to be
his inaugural artist.

768
00:45:56.053 --> 00:45:57.681
I'm sure you will be.

769
00:45:59.290 --> 00:46:00.986
He'll need an assistant.

770
00:46:01.259 --> 00:46:02.921
And you could use an upgrade.

771
00:46:02.994 --> 00:46:04.792
Yeah. I'm fine where I am.

772
00:46:08.599 --> 00:46:11.569
Darling. um. come with me.

773
00:46:11.736 --> 00:46:13.329
I need to talk to you.

774
00:46:13.404 --> 00:46:15.032
I think I should go
rescue your friend

775
00:46:15.106 --> 00:46:16.301
- from Andrea.
- Listen. I...

776
00:46:17.608 --> 00:46:19.304
I have to show you something.

777
00:46:20.778 --> 00:46:24.078
The last time we went somewhere
to talk. it didn't go so well.

778
00:46:26.317 --> 00:46:31.017
I think we've both come
a long way from Paris.

779
00:46:32.256 --> 00:46:33.280
Haven't we?

780
00:46:36.761 --> 00:46:37.761
Come on.

781
00:46:52.376 --> 00:46:54.470
So. are you gonna
apologize now or what?

782
00:46:59.517 --> 00:47:00.541
[sighs]

783
00:47:06.023 --> 00:47:07.023
I'm sorry.

784
00:47:07.391 --> 00:47:09.553
I'm so sorry. Whitney.

785
00:47:09.994 --> 00:47:11.860
I was an ass.

786
00:47:14.231 --> 00:47:15.790
There's not a... a day goes by

787
00:47:15.866 --> 00:47:19.826
where I don't regret
what happened in Paris.

788
00:47:21.939 --> 00:47:26.877
That I could do that to
any woman. but to you.

789
00:47:27.945 --> 00:47:30.380
the perfect...

790
00:47:30.881 --> 00:47:32.782
perfect woman.

791
00:47:35.820 --> 00:47:36.820
I'm sorry.

792
00:47:38.989 --> 00:47:40.048
Will you forgive me?

793
00:47:43.094 --> 00:47:46.064
Please. please forgive me.

794
00:47:47.698 --> 00:47:48.757
[whispering] Furkat.

795
00:47:49.633 --> 00:47:52.467
- Stop. Get up. You're embarrassing me.
- Not until you forgive me.

796
00:47:54.004 --> 00:47:57.065
- Oh. my God. stop it. You're... Stand up.
- Not until you forgive me!

797
00:48:23.934 --> 00:48:24.934
What is happening?

798
00:48:25.035 --> 00:48:27.527
It's all for you.

799
00:48:29.206 --> 00:48:30.765
Furkat. please. just stand up.

800
00:48:30.841 --> 00:48:32.332
- Do you forgive me?
- Yes.

801
00:48:32.510 --> 00:48:35.309
- No. you don't.
- Please. Furkat. just stand up.

802
00:48:35.379 --> 00:48:36.847
- Say it.
- Say what?

803
00:48:37.081 --> 00:48:39.949
- Say you forgive me.
- I do. I forgive you. Just get up!

804
00:48:40.017 --> 00:48:42.009
I forgive you. I forgive
you. I forgive you.

805
00:48:45.523 --> 00:48:47.515
[applause. cheering]

806
00:49:04.442 --> 00:49:05.933
Stop. Stop.

807
00:49:14.852 --> 00:49:17.344
[grunts. exhales]

808
00:49:18.222 --> 00:49:21.556
So. how long have
you known F... Lindsay?

809
00:49:22.393 --> 00:49:25.886
[chuckles] Uh. we met a
few months ago at Basel.

810
00:49:27.932 --> 00:49:29.594
He's very talented.

811
00:49:30.935 --> 00:49:32.028
That's funny.

812
00:49:32.803 --> 00:49:34.431
He says the same
thing about you.

813
00:49:35.139 --> 00:49:36.835
- He does?
- Mm-hm.

814
00:49:38.309 --> 00:49:40.574
He said that you
have an amazing eye.

815
00:49:46.450 --> 00:49:48.646
[laughter. indistinct chatter]

816
00:49:48.719 --> 00:49:50.187
They are so beautiful.

817
00:49:57.761 --> 00:49:59.161
Yeah. I was just thinking that.

818
00:50:01.332 --> 00:50:02.332
You should join them.

819
00:50:02.800 --> 00:50:04.098
[chuckles]

820
00:50:07.338 --> 00:50:08.397
Prefer to watch?

821
00:50:11.408 --> 00:50:12.467
Yeah. me. too.

822
00:50:17.014 --> 00:50:21.509
You know. I used to want to model
for Lindsay. when I was younger.

823
00:50:21.719 --> 00:50:23.517
[laughs]

824
00:50:24.455 --> 00:50:26.890
- When you were younger.
- Well. I meant...

825
00:50:26.957 --> 00:50:29.927
Yeah. I know what you meant.

826
00:50:32.396 --> 00:50:33.523
[wine pouring]

827
00:50:34.398 --> 00:50:35.398
And now?

828
00:50:36.867 --> 00:50:38.665
I don't want to be
looked at anymore.

829
00:50:38.903 --> 00:50:40.872
I want to be the one
that does the looking.

830
00:50:41.872 --> 00:50:43.704
Well. that is where
all the power lies.

831
00:50:44.808 --> 00:50:45.935
[laughs]

832
00:50:48.212 --> 00:50:50.238
If you could have
everything you wanted.

833
00:50:51.916 --> 00:50:52.940
what would it look like?

834
00:50:58.656 --> 00:50:59.851
Well...

835
00:51:02.626 --> 00:51:07.064
Somebody would give me the money
to start my own gallery where I could...

836
00:51:09.867 --> 00:51:11.631
foster new artists.

837
00:51:11.702 --> 00:51:13.227
Younger artists.

838
00:51:13.304 --> 00:51:17.674
So much of what I see now
feels recycled. redundant...

839
00:51:17.975 --> 00:51:22.208
built for an audience that already exists
as opposed to in search of a new one.

840
00:51:23.547 --> 00:51:26.745
I'd want to promote artists
that are digging deeper.

841
00:51:26.817 --> 00:51:30.345
that are looking for something amorphous
that haunts them. that haunts me.

842
00:51:30.421 --> 00:51:33.255
that I just don't have
the language for. [laughs]

843
00:51:35.826 --> 00:51:37.337
Oh. my God. I sound
like a fucking idiot.

844
00:51:37.361 --> 00:51:39.023
No. no. That's...

845
00:51:42.800 --> 00:51:43.893
That's beautiful.

846
00:51:48.872 --> 00:51:50.431
I've had enough. I think.

847
00:51:51.141 --> 00:51:52.141
[chuckles]

848
00:51:55.245 --> 00:51:56.245
Ah.

849
00:51:56.814 --> 00:51:58.339
[in British accent]
Hello. Lindsay.

850
00:51:59.850 --> 00:52:00.681
Excuse me. Dashiell.

851
00:52:00.751 --> 00:52:04.244
Do you mind if I.
um... [clicks tongue]

852
00:52:04.321 --> 00:52:06.119
just borrow this
one for a moment?

853
00:52:26.744 --> 00:52:28.474
God. you're so beautiful.

854
00:52:30.948 --> 00:52:32.473
I really missed you.

855
00:52:56.140 --> 00:52:58.974
I missed this so much.

